3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The inverse dynamic whole-body controller used in the framework can be considered as an AI-based approach for coordinating all joints, including the wheels. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not explicitly mentioned, the framework may involve machine learning techniques for generating and tracking the motion of the robot. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper does not explicitly mention the use of computer vision, but it is possible that vision-based sensing could be used for obstacle detection and avoidance.
